                Given without grace.
            </translation>
        </marginalia>
        
        <marginalia hand="Italian">
            <language ident="LA">
                <position book_orientation="0" place="right_margin">
                    <marginalia_text>
                        Debes hic animaduertere cu[m] dicat aut cu[m] eo, quonia[m] ante dixit nocte hoc ita no[n] esse debere, sed die qui ☉e in 4 co[n]stituto esse no[n] p[otes]t noli in re tam aperta cavillari 
                    </marginalia_text>
                </position>
            </language>
            <translation>
                You ought to pay attention here when he says 'or with that', since before he said that in the nights this ought not to be thus,
                but on the day which cannot be in the fourth position with the Sun, do not jest in the matter so openly. <!--JG: Unsure-->
            </translation>
        </marginalia>
        
        <marginalia hand="English_secretary">
